In [21]:
df_grouped = df.groupby("SalesPerson")["Unit Sell Price"].sum().reset_index()


plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))

plt.pie(
    df_grouped["Unit Sell Price"], labels=df_grouped["SalesPerson"], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, counterclock=False, wedgeprops={'width': 0.6}  )

plt.title("SalesPerson wise Total Unit Sell Price Percentage ", fontsize=16)
plt.show()
In [22]:
plt.figure(figsize=(18,8))

df_product = df.groupby("Product Container")["Unit Sell Price"].sum().reset_index()

ax = sns.barplot(x="Product Container", y="Unit Sell Price", data=df_product, color = 'goldenrod')

plt.title("Product Container wise Total Unit Sell Price", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Product Container", fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel("Unit Sell Price", fontsize=14)

plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=14)
ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0], fontsize=14)
plt.show()

In [30]:
plt.figure(figsize=(18,7))

df_Customer_ID = (
    df.groupby("Customer ID")["Unit Sell Price"].sum().reset_index().sort_values(by="Unit Sell Price", ascending=False).head(10))

ax = sns.lineplot(x="Customer ID", y="Unit Sell Price", data=df_Customer_ID, marker='o', color = 'red')

plt.title("Top Customer ID wise Total Unit Sell Price", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Customer ID", fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel("Unit Sell Price", fontsize=14)
plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=14)

for i, row in df_Customer_ID.iterrows():
    ax.text(row["Customer ID"], row["Unit Sell Price"], 
            f'{row["Unit Sell Price"]:.0f}', 
            ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=14)

plt.show()
